          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 22-m and 48-m flight paths at Brookhaven",
                "fast chopper facility. GeLi detectors were used to",
                "measure absolute gamma-ray intensities due to neutron",
                "capture in individual resonance of 173Yb. Gamma rays",
                "were gated using time of flight information."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PGS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The spins of resonances were determined by",
                "examination of the low- and high-energy primary gamma",
                "rays. Because the spin and parity of the target",
                "nucleus are 5/2+, the interaction of s-wave neutrons",
                "with 173Yb would excite 2+ and 3+ states.",
                "Observations of strong transitions to either 4+ or 1+",
                "low-lying final states would indicate that spin of",
                "resonance is 3+ or 1+."
              ]
            }
          ],
